# Frontend Standards

Every feature must contain exactly:
api/
components/
hooks/
pages/
store/
types/
constants/
utils/

No standalone files directly inside a feature folder.

TypeScript:
- strict: true must be enabled in tsconfig.json
- Never use `any` without an explicit eslint-disable comment and justification
- All props typed with interfaces

Components:
- PascalCase filenames and exports
- One component per file
- No business logic inside components
- Components call hooks; hooks call API functions

Hooks:
- useXxx.ts naming convention
- Data fetching via React Query inside hooks
- Never call APIs directly from components

State management:
- Server/API state → React Query only
- Shared client state → Zustand store slice in feature/store/
- Local UI state (one component) → useState
- Never store server data in Zustand

Imports:
- Absolute imports only using @/ alias
- Never use deep relative imports (../../..)
- Never import from another feature directly

Shared code:
- Reusable components → frontend/src/shared/components/
- Reusable hooks → frontend/src/shared/hooks/
- Shared types → frontend/src/shared/types/
